The paper deals with database mappings and their semantics, which falls under the scope of computer science databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of logical languages and behavioral equivalences, which are topics covered in computer science logic (cs.LO). The use of monads and endofunctors in the paper suggests a connection to computer science data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses query definitions and rewriting, which are topics covered in computer science programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses data integration models, which are relevant to computer science artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
